## When suggesting code

1. Check `TODO.md` to confirm the task is in the current phase.
2. Read the relevant spec section for requirements.
3. Check for an existing ADR; if a new architectural decision is 
   needed, propose an ADR before writing the code.
4. Write tests in the same PR as the feature.
5. Update `TODO.md` when items change status.
6. Reference spec sections in commit messages 
   (e.g., `feat(api): PATCH /annotations with If-Match (spec §10)`).

---

## When in doubt

- Cite the relevant section of `docs/spec/visionloop-spec.md`.
- Surface ambiguity rather than guessing.
- Prefer the boring, well-tested option over the clever one.
- Ship the flywheel correctly. Two models. Production-grade.
